<subSubSection pageId="111" pageNumber="112" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="111" pageNumber="112">
82. 
<taxonomicName LSID="F20DB0EE-C84D-5E82-B2DD-6E0147E6DA93" authority="P. Silva &amp; Teles, Bol. Soc. Brot., ser. 2, 53: 515, t. 1. 1980. (Silva and Teles 1980: 515)." authorityName="P. Silva &amp; Teles, Bol. Soc. Brot., ser. 2, 53: 515, t. 1. 1980. (Silva and Teles" authorityYear="1980" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus fernandesii" order="Solanales" pageId="111" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fernandesii">Convolvulus fernandesii P.Silva &amp; Teles, Bol. Soc. Brot., ser. 2, 53: 515, t. 1. 1980. (Silva and Teles 1980: 515).</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="111" pageNumber="112" type="type">
<paragraph pageId="111" pageNumber="112">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="111" pageNumber="112">
PORTUGAL, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">Pinto da Silva, Teles &amp; Pina</emphasis>
9337 (holotype LISE 94263!).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="112" pageNumber="113" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="112" pageNumber="113">
<pageBreakToken pageId="112" pageNumber="113" start="start">Description</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="112" pageNumber="113">
A scrambling or twining shrub, old stems woody, glabrescent, young stems pubescent. Leaves petiolate, 1-6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5-3.5 cm, elliptic or oblong-elliptic, retuse, entire, base rounded to subcordate, puberulent on the nerves beneath but soon glabrescent; petiole 1-2.5 cm. Flowers 3-6 in axillary, pedunculate cymes; peduncles 1-2 cm; bracteoles 5-9 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-2.5 mm, oblanceolate; pedicels 5-10 mm; sepals 6-9 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-3.5 mm, obovate to elliptic, mucronate, puberulent, inner sepals scarious, puberulent near base only; corolla 1.5-1.7 cm, white, sinuate, midpetaline bands tomentose; filaments glandular near base; ovary glabrous; style glabrous, divided c. 4 mm above base, stigmas c. 2 mm. Capsule and seeds unknown. [
<bibRefCitation author="Silvestre, S" editor="Talevera, S" journalOrPublisher="Real Jardin Botanico, CSIC, Madrid" pageId="211" pageNumber="212" pagination="252 - 273" refId="B337" refString="Silvestre, S, 2012. Convolvulus. In: Talevera, S, Andres, C, Arista, M, Fernandes Piedra, MP, Gallego, MJ, Ortiz, PL, Romero Zarco, C, Salgueiro, FJ, Silvestre, S, Quinanar, A, Eds., Flora Iberica volume 11: Gentianaceae to Boraginaceae. Real Jardin Botanico, CSIC, Madrid: 252 - 273" title="Convolvulus." volumeTitle="Flora Iberica volume 11: Gentianaceae to Boraginaceae." year="2012">Silvestre 2012</bibRefCitation>
: 260]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="112" pageNumber="113" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Portugal: Cabo Espichel. Rare, narrow endemic of dolomitic rock at 125 m.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="112" pageNumber="113" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Although seeds are clearly visible on the image of the type specimen no description has been provided.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="112" pageNumber="113">
This species is related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L., Sp. Pl. 155. 1753. (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus canariensis" order="Solanales" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="canariensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Convolvulus canariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its allies from the Canary Islands and Madeira. It differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L., Sp. Pl. 155. 1753. (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus canariensis" order="Solanales" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="canariensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Convolvulus canariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its near glabrous leaves and from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="F. Dietr., Nachtr. Vollst. Lex. Gaertn. 2: 377. 1816. (Dietrich" authorityYear="1816" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus massonii" order="Solanales" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="massonii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Convolvulus massonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its shorter sepals, smaller corolla and glabrous ovary. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brouss. ex Link, Phys. Beschr. Canar. Ins. 145. 1828 [1825]. (Buch" authorityYear="1828" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus volubilis" order="Solanales" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="volubilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Convolvulus volubilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the leaves are oblong-elliptic, not linear lanceolate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
